%S A183634 44,136,452,1576,5684,21016,79172,302536,1168724,4552696,17848292,
%T A183634 70313896,278034164,1102505176,4381191812,17438411656,69494842004,
%U A183634 277203478456,1106487293732,4418971411816,17654956552244,70557047312536,282039869338052,1127594551170376,4508683493244884
%N A183634 Number of (n+1) X 2 0..3 arrays with every 2 x 2 subblock summing to 6.
%C A183634 Conjecture: Number of (n+1) X (k+1) 0..p arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 2p is Sum_{i=1..(p+1)} i^(n+1)*(p+2-i)^(k+1) - 2*Sum_{i=1..p} i^(n+1)*(p+1-i)^(k+1) + Sum_{i=1..(p-1)} i^(n+1)*(p-i)^(k+1). - _Zhuorui He_, Jun 20 2026
%H A183634 Zhuorui He, <a href="/A183634/b183634.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000</a> (first 200 terms from R. H. Hardin)
%H A183634 Christian Krause, <a href="/A183634/a183634.txt">Proof of formula</a>, Jun 20 2026
%H A183634 <a href="/index/Rec#order_04">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (10,-35,50,-24).
%F A183634 a(n) = 10*a(n-1) - 35*a(n-2) + 50*a(n-3) - 24*a(n-4).
%F A183634 From _Colin Barker_, Feb 27 2018: (Start)
%F A183634 G.f.: 4*x*(11 - 76*x + 158*x^2 - 96*x^3) / ((1 - x)*(1 - 2*x)*(1 - 3*x)*(1 - 4*x)).
%F A183634 a(n) = 2 + 2^(2+n) + 2*3^(1+n) + 4^(1+n).
%F A183634 (End) [proved by _Christian Krause_, Jun 20 2026]
%e A183634 Some solutions for 3 X 2:
%e A183634 ..0..3....2..2....0..3....1..3....0..2....1..3....2..1....3..0....1..3....3..1
%e A183634 ..3..0....0..2....0..3....0..2....1..3....1..1....2..1....0..3....2..0....1..1
%e A183634 ..1..2....3..1....3..0....2..2....2..0....2..2....3..0....2..1....1..3....1..3
%o A183634 (PARI) f(n, k, p)=sum(i=1, p+1, i^(n+1)*(p+2-i)^(k+1))-2*sum(i=1, p, i^(n+1)*(p+1-i)^(k+1))+sum(i=1, p-1, i^(n+1)*(p-i)^(k+1)) \\ f(n, k, p) is conjectured to be number of (n+1) X (k+1) 0..p arrays with every 2 X 2 subblock summing to 2p.
%o A183634 A183634(n) = f(n, 1, 3) \\ This is proved using the proved formula above.
%o A183634 \\ _Zhuorui He_, Jun 20 2026
